WEBVTT

0
00:00:00.129 --> 00:00:02.009
When someone contacts the service desk,

1
00:00:02.289 --> 00:00:03.089
whether by phone,

2
00:00:03.170 --> 00:00:03.569
chat,

3
00:00:03.769 --> 00:00:04.078
Teams,

4
00:00:04.090 --> 00:00:04.929
or another channel,

5
00:00:05.210 --> 00:00:06.610
it starts with an interaction.

6
00:00:06.889 --> 00:00:10.109
The interaction captures who contacted you and what they need.

7
00:00:10.409 --> 00:00:12.250
It's important to understand whether the person is

8
00:00:12.250 --> 00:00:14.710
an internal user or an external contact.

9
00:00:15.210 --> 00:00:16.760
If they're an internal user,

10
00:00:16.850 --> 00:00:20.489
you will typically create an incident or a request if follow-up work is needed.

11
00:00:21.200 --> 00:00:21.590
Of course,

12
00:00:21.729 --> 00:00:24.110
not every interaction requires follow-up work.

13
00:00:24.370 --> 00:00:26.989
If the issue is resolved during the initial contact,

14
00:00:27.290 --> 00:00:28.770
the interaction can be closed.

15
00:00:32.080 --> 00:00:33.299
For external contacts,

16
00:00:33.389 --> 00:00:34.950
the process is slightly different.

17
00:00:35.189 --> 00:00:36.569
You'll first create a case.

18
00:00:36.790 --> 00:00:39.849
The case becomes the customer facing record for the external user.

19
00:00:40.069 --> 00:00:41.380
If additional work is needed,

20
00:00:41.549 --> 00:00:45.169
you can then create an incident or request for internal teams to resolve.

21
00:00:47.349 --> 00:00:48.430
As work progresses,

22
00:00:48.770 --> 00:00:52.229
updates from the incident or request are reflected automatically in the case,

23
00:00:52.560 --> 00:00:54.959
so external customers can track progress without

24
00:00:54.959 --> 00:00:57.880
needing visibility into internal IT processes.

25
00:00:59.599 --> 00:01:01.020
Always start with an interaction,

26
00:01:01.520 --> 00:01:03.259
then create the right type of work,

27
00:01:03.759 --> 00:01:06.000
an incident or request for internal users.

28
00:01:06.680 --> 00:01:08.459
A case for external users

29
00:01:08.639 --> 00:01:10.199
or resolve the request directly.